Manchester United have struck an agreement with the agent of Sporting Lisbon star Bruno Fernandes. That’s according to journalist Nicolo Schira, who claims the Portuguese international has agreed a five-year contract worth £98k per week. “Total agreement between Bruno Fernandes agent (Miguel Pinho) and Manchester United until 2025 (£5.1million a year),” Schira tweeted. “They’ve told to Sporting about Bruno’s desire to play in Premier League. Tomorrow, Manchester United will work to reach agreement with Sporting and close the deal.” It’s believed Ed Woodward and his team will lodge an offer in the region of £65million today. Why Manchester United may pull out of deal for £60m star Manchester City sign 18-year-old winger from Sporting Lisbon Jorginho moving to Manchester City - Agent